author: JEFF FLETCHER
title: What went right, wrong in Angels' season that came up just short?
text:
BY JEFF FLETCHER / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 5, 2015 Updated: 1:00 p.m. The Angels had high hopes for 2015 after winning 98 games last year, but they came up one game short of returning to the playoffs, winning 85 games.
Whether this team underachieved or finished about where it should have been based on its talent is debatable. In fact, you can even make a case, based on all the things that went wrong, that they may have overachieved.
Like any team in any season, there were pluses and minuses. Check out the slideshow to see what went right, what went wrong.
Contact the writer: jlfletcher@ocregister.com
